<div class="context-differential">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 900 260">
    <!-- Title -->
    <text x="450" y="40" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="#1A1A1A">
        Context Window Mismatch
    </text>
    <text x="450" y="60" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="12" fill="#6B6B6B">
        Long inputs can overflow the filter, while the LLM still sees the full conversation.
    </text>

    <!-- LLM context bar (full) -->
    <text x="110" y="105"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="12" fill="#6B6B6B">
        LLM context window
    </text>

    <!-- LLM bar background -->
    <rect x="100" y="115" width="700" height="38" rx="12"
            fill="#FAF8F5" stroke="#E8E5DF" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Region seen by both filter and LLM -->
    <rect x="100" y="115" width="480" height="38" rx="12"
            fill="#F7F4EE" stroke="none"/>

    <text x="340" y="138" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="11" fill="#6B6B6B">
        Benign and earlier turns (seen by filter and LLM)
    </text>

    <!-- Adversarial tail only LLM sees -->
    <rect x="580" y="115" width="220" height="38" rx="12"
            fill="#FFF1E6" stroke="#F05D23" stroke-width="1.5"/>

    <text x="690" y="135" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="11" fill="#F05D23">
        Overflow / adversarial tail (LLM only)
    </text>

    <!-- Filter context bar (shorter) -->
    <text x="110" y="180"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="12" fill="#6B6B6B">
        Filter / guardrail context window
    </text>

    <rect x="100" y="190" width="480" height="34" rx="12"
            fill="#FAF8F5" stroke="#C2BFB6" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>

    <text x="340" y="211" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="11" fill="#6B6B6B">
        Filter only sees this prefix
    </text>

    <!-- Cutoff marker -->
    <line x1="580" y1="108" x2="580" y2="205"
            stroke="#C2BFB6" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 4"/>

    <text x="600" y="200"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="10" fill="#6B6B6B">
        Filter cut-off
    </text>

    <!-- Note at bottom -->
    <text x="450" y="240" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="'DM Sans', sans-serif"
            font-size="11" fill="#6B6B6B">
        By flooding the input length, the attacker pushes critical instructions into a region
        the LLM can see but the filter cannot.
    </text>
    </svg>
</div>